ciscoDlcSwitchMIB.name: ciscoDlcSwitchMIB
ciscoDlcSwitchMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W. Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-fras@cisco.com
ciscoDlcSwitchMIB.description: This is the MIB module for objects used to manage FRAS sessions to the endstation. These objects are specific to downstream or enduster sessions only. It does not contain objects supported by the FRAS-HOST MIB which are specific to upstream or host-end sessions.

SAP.name: SAP
SAP.description: Service Access Point - is a term that denotes the means by which a user entity in layer n+1 accesses a service of a provider entity in layer n.

SdlcAddress.name: SdlcAddress
SdlcAddress.description: A hexadecimal address assigned to a secondary poll station of an SDLC device.

frasBnnSdlcConTable.name: frasBnnSdlcConTable
frasBnnSdlcConTable.description: This table contains mapping information for each SDLC Link Station in a FRAS-BNN to SDLC connection. All entries are derived entirely from the router configuration.

frasBnnSdlcConEntry.name: frasBnnSdlcConEntry
frasBnnSdlcConEntry.description: This table contains the entries defined for a specific SDLC Link Station in a BNN-SDLC configuration.

bnnSdlcConAddress.name: bnnSdlcConAddress
bnnSdlcConAddress.description: This value is the poll address of the secondary link station for this SDLC link. It uniquely identifies the SDLC link station within a single SDLC port.

bnnSdlcConState.name: bnnSdlcConState
bnnSdlcConState.description: Contains the FRAS state of the Link Station. reset - no activity testSent - TEST Frames sent xidexchg - XID exchange in progress connrqsent - Connect request sent sigstnwait - Signal station wait state connrspwait - Connect response wait state connrspsent - Connect response sent contacted - Session established discwait - Disconnect wait state

bnnSdlcConDlci.name: bnnSdlcConDlci
bnnSdlcConDlci.description: The Data Link Connection Identifier used for this particular connection.

bnnSdlcConFRInterface.name: bnnSdlcConFRInterface
bnnSdlcConFRInterface.description: This is the Frame-Relay interface which the SDLC Link Station is using to connect to the Host.

bnnSdlcConLocalSap.name: bnnSdlcConLocalSap
bnnSdlcConLocalSap.description: The Local SAP for this SDLC station's corresponding LLC session to the host.

bnnSdlcConRemoteSap.name: bnnSdlcConRemoteSap
bnnSdlcConRemoteSap.description: The Remote SAP for this SDLC station's corresponding LLC session to the host.

frasBnnLlcConTable.name: frasBnnLlcConTable
frasBnnLlcConTable.description: This table contains information for each End Station in a FRAS-BNN to LLC connection. The entries are derived entirely from the router configuration.

frasBnnLlcConEntry.name: frasBnnLlcConEntry
frasBnnLlcConEntry.description: This table contains information for a specific End Station's connection state in a BNN-LLC connection.

bnnLlcConDeviceMacAddress.name: bnnLlcConDeviceMacAddress
bnnLlcConDeviceMacAddress.description: This value is the End Station's Local Mac-Address.

bnnLlcConLanInterface.name: bnnLlcConLanInterface
bnnLlcConLanInterface.description: This is the physical interace which the End Station is attached to.

bnnLlcConDlci.name: bnnLlcConDlci
bnnLlcConDlci.description: The Data Link Connection Identifier associated with the corresponding LLC2 session over Frame-Relay to the host.

bnnLlcConState.name: bnnLlcConState
bnnLlcConState.description: Contains the FRAS state of the Link Station. reset - no activity testSent - TEST Frames sent xidexchg - XID exchange in progress connrqsent - Connect request sent sigstnwait - Signal station wait state connrspwait - Connect response wait state connrspsent - Connect response sent contacted - Session established discwait - Disconnect wait state

bnnLlcConLocalMacAddress.name: bnnLlcConLocalMacAddress
bnnLlcConLocalMacAddress.description: The Mac-Address configured as the End Station's target or Remote address.

frasBanSdlcConTable.name: frasBanSdlcConTable
frasBanSdlcConTable.description: This table contains information for each SDLC Link Station in a FRAS-BAN to SDLC connection. The entries are derived entirely from the router configuration.

frasBanSdlcConEntry.name: frasBanSdlcConEntry
frasBanSdlcConEntry.description: This table contains information for a specific SDLC Link Station in a configured for a BAN connection.

banSdlcConLocalInterface.name: banSdlcConLocalInterface
banSdlcConLocalInterface.description: This is the physical interface the SDLC Link Stations are connected to.

banSdlcConAddress.name: banSdlcConAddress
banSdlcConAddress.description: This value is the poll address of the secondary link station for this SDLC link. It uniquely identifies the SDLC link station within a single SDLC port.

banSdlcConBanDlciMac.name: banSdlcConBanDlciMac
banSdlcConBanDlciMac.description: The End Station's target or Remote mac-address.

banSdlcConDlci.name: banSdlcConDlci
banSdlcConDlci.description: The Data Link Connection Identifier for the corresponding LLC2 session over Frame-Relay to the host.

banSdlcConState.name: banSdlcConState
banSdlcConState.description: Contains the FRAS state of the Link Station. reset - no activity testSent- TEST Frames sent xidexchg - XID exchange in progress connrqsent - Connect request sent sigstnwait - Signal station wait state connrspwait - Connect response wait state connrspsent - Connect response sent contacted - Session established discwait - Disconnect wait state

banSdlcConVmac.name: banSdlcConVmac
banSdlcConVmac.description: The End Station's virtual Mac-Address which is comprised of a TR formatted template and the SDLC Link Station address appended on the last nibble.

banSdlcConBniAddress.name: banSdlcConBniAddress
banSdlcConBniAddress.description: BNI is Boundary Node Identifier which is the FRAS-BAN connection's Remote address in TR-format. It is by default 4fff.0000.0000

frasBanLlcConTable.name: frasBanLlcConTable
frasBanLlcConTable.description: This table contains information for each LAN attached End Station in a FRAS-BAN to LAN connection. The entries are from endstations which have their destination mac-addresses as the BAN-DLCI-MAC address.

frasBanLlcConEntry.name: frasBanLlcConEntry
frasBanLlcConEntry.description: This table contains information for a specific LAN attached End Station.

banLlcEndstnLocalMac.name: banLlcEndstnLocalMac
banLlcEndstnLocalMac.description: This value is the End Station's Local Mac-Address.

banLlcBanDlciMac.name: banLlcBanDlciMac
banLlcBanDlciMac.description: This value is the End Station's Remote Mac-Address. It is also the FRAS-BAN connection's Local Mac-Address.

banLlcConDlci.name: banLlcConDlci
banLlcConDlci.description: The Data Link Connection Identifier associated with the corresponding LLC2 session over Frame-Relay to the host.

banLlcConState.name: banLlcConState
banLlcConState.description: Contains the FRAS state of the Link Station. reset - no activity testSent- TEST Frames sent xidexchg - XID exchange in progress connrqsent - Connect request sent sigstnwait - Signal station wait state connrspwait - Connect response wait state connrspsent - Connect response sent contacted - Session established discwait - Disconnect wait state

banLlcConFrInterface.name: banLlcConFrInterface
banLlcConFrInterface.description: This is the Frame-Relay interface for this particular session.

banLlcBniAddress.name: banLlcBniAddress
banLlcBniAddress.description: This value is the FRAS-BAN connection's Target Mac-Address. It is by default 4fff.0000.0000

banLlcConFrLocalSap.name: banLlcConFrLocalSap
banLlcConFrLocalSap.description: The Local SAP of the corresponding LLC2 session over Frame-Relay to the host.

banLlcConFrRemoteSap.name: banLlcConFrRemoteSap
banLlcConFrRemoteSap.description: The Remote SAP of the corresponding LLC2 session over Frame-Relay to the host.

ciscoDlcSwitchCoreCompliance.name: ciscoDlcSwitchCoreCompliance
ciscoDlcSwitchCoreCompliance.description: The core compliance statement for all FRAS connections.

frasBnnSdlcGroup.name: frasBnnSdlcGroup
frasBnnSdlcGroup.description: The frasBnnSdlcGroup defines objects which are common to the BNN SDLC of all compliant connections.

frasBnnLlcGroup.name: frasBnnLlcGroup
frasBnnLlcGroup.description: The frasBnnLlcGroup defines objects which are common to the BNN LLC of all compliant connections.

frasBanSdlcGroup.name: frasBanSdlcGroup
frasBanSdlcGroup.description: The frasBanSdlcGroup defines objects which are common to the BAN SDLC of all compliant connections.

frasBanLlcGroup.name: frasBanLlcGroup
frasBanLlcGroup.description: The frasBanLlcGroup defines objects which are common to the BAN LLC of all compliant connections.
